<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="48" pageNumber="79">Status. Pontocaspian species, identity uncertain.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="48" pageNumber="79">
Type locality. Caspian Sea, &quot;near Krasnojarsk&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Westerlund, CA" journalOrPublisher="Nachrichtsblatt der Deutschen Malakozoologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="87" pageNumber="118" pagination="35 - 47" title="Malacologische Bemerkungen und Beschreibungen." url="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/15598774" volume="34" year="1902 a">Westerlund 1902a</bibRefCitation>
). This statement is clearly erroneous since Krasnojarsk is situated in Siberia. Most probably, Westerlund meant Krasnovodsk (nowadays Turkmenbashi) in Turkmenistan (
<bibRefCitation author="Vinarski, MV" journalOrPublisher="Ruthenica" pageId="86" pageNumber="117" pagination="79 - 108" title="Type materials of freshwater gastropod species described by CA Westerlund and accepted in current malacological taxonomy: a taxonomic and nomenclatorial study." url="http://www.ruthenica.com/documents/VOL23_Vinarski_et_al_79-108_standard.pdf" volume="23" year="2013">Vinarski et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="49" pageNumber="80">
<pageBreakToken pageId="49" pageNumber="80" start="start">Distribution</pageBreakToken>
. Endemic to the Caspian Sea. This species was mentioned from depths between 200 and 300 m in the South Caspian Basin of Azerbaijan (
<bibRefCitation author="Mirzoev, GS" journalOrPublisher="International Journal of Zoological Studies" pageId="79" pageNumber="110" pagination="43 - 48" title="Zoobenthos distribution patterns in the deepwater horizon of Azerbaijan sector of the Caspian Sea." url="http://www.zoologyjournals.com/download/74/1-7-29-696.pdf" volume="2" year="2017">Mirzoev and Alekperov 2017</bibRefCitation>
, who reported the species as 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Turricaspia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Turricaspia marginata" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="49" pageNumber="80" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="marginata">Turricaspia marginata</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="49" pageNumber="80">
Taxonomic notes. The status of this species is uncertain. The illustrations of the type material by 
<bibRefCitation author="Vinarski, MV" journalOrPublisher="Ruthenica" pageId="86" pageNumber="117" pagination="79 - 108" title="Type materials of freshwater gastropod species described by CA Westerlund and accepted in current malacological taxonomy: a taxonomic and nomenclatorial study." url="http://www.ruthenica.com/documents/VOL23_Vinarski_et_al_79-108_standard.pdf" volume="23" year="2013">Vinarski et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
suggest a tentative placement in the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Laevicaspia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laevicaspia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="49" pageNumber="80" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Laevicaspia</taxonomicName>
. It shows close similarities with 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. sieversii" pageId="49" pageNumber="80" rank="species" species="sieversii">L. sieversii</taxonomicName>
(Clessin in Dybowski, 1887). A careful revision of the species is required to clarify its taxonomic status and systematic placement.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="conservation">
<paragraph pageId="49" pageNumber="80">Conservation status. Not assessed.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
